<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">February 24, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-february-24-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-249849 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Edward_Gorey_takes_on_Henri_Bendels_window-150x150.jpg" alt="edward gorey" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/m-is-for-mortality-lessons-from-edward-gorey-on-his-hundredth-birthday" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Lessons from Edward Gorey</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.bookforum.com/print/3103/a-history-of-violence-61617" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Jamie Hood on Gisèle Pelicot, Virginie Despentes, and post-#MeToo narratives</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.wired.com/story/plaintext-ai-doomers-mcneal/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">How playwrights are responding to AI</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-february-24-2025/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
